<!doctype html>
<html>
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<title>H38-A001 CNC ROI Worksheet</title>
<style>
  body{font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-size:11pt;margin:14px;background:#fff;color:#111827}
  table{border-collapse:collapse;width:1280px;table-layout:fixed}
  th,td{border:1px solid #b7c3d0;padding:8px 10px;vertical-align:top;white-space:normal;word-wrap:break-word;line-height:1.35;mso-number-format:"\@"}
  th{background:#dbeafe;font-weight:700;color:#0f172a}.title{background:#1f2937;color:#fff;font-size:16pt;text-align:left;padding:12px}.sub{background:#f8fafc;color:#475569;font-style:italic}.narrow{text-align:center}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<table>
<colgroup><col style="width:145px"><col style="width:175px"><col style="width:215px"><col style="width:190px"><col style="width:310px"><col style="width:115px"><col style="width:130px"></colgroup>
<tr><th class="title" colspan="7">Highway 38 Solutions - H38-A001 Shop / CNC ROI and Vendor Worksheet</th></tr>
<tr><td class="sub" colspan="7">Use this worksheet before asking vendors for a quote so cycle time, idle reasons, guarding scope, and acceptance testing are not guessed.</td></tr>
<tr><th>Item</th><th>Current Estimate</th><th>Needed Before Quote</th><th>Risk</th><th>Vendor Question</th><th>Status</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
<tr><td>Cycle time</td><td>Unknown / guessed</td><td>Actual average cycle</td><td>Wrong payback math</td><td>What cycle target is realistic for this part and process?</td><td class="narrow">Collect data</td><td>Measure for one week.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Idle time</td><td>High</td><td>Idle reason log</td><td>Solving the wrong problem</td><td>Which idle reasons does your proposal actually remove?</td><td class="narrow">Collect data</td><td>Use idle tracker.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Part weight</td><td>Unknown</td><td>Weight and grip points</td><td>Wrong gripper choice</td><td>What gripper style is required?</td><td class="narrow">Missing</td><td>Need part examples.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Infeed</td><td>Manual rack</td><td>Preferred presentation</td><td>Robot waits for parts</td><td>What infeed options are included?</td><td class="narrow">Open</td><td>Tray, conveyor, rack, or bin.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Guarding</td><td>Not defined</td><td>Vendor scope</td><td>Safety gap</td><td>What guarding and validation are included?</td><td class="narrow">Vendor</td><td>Qualified vendor required.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Acceptance test</td><td>Not defined</td><td>Pass/fail test</td><td>No success target</td><td>What proves the cell works?</td><td class="narrow">Open</td><td>Cycle, quality, fault recovery.</td></tr>
</table>
</body>
</html>
